{"number":"3.4601","name":"work authorization","definitions":"a permission and direction, typically written, to begin work on a specific schedule activity or work package or control account. It is a method for sanctioning project work to ensure that the work is done by the identified organization, at the right time, and in the proper sequence."}
{"number":"3.4602","name":"work authorization system","definitions":"a subsystem of the overall project management system. It is a collection of formal documented procedures that defines how project work will be authorized (committed) to ensure that the work is done by the identified organization, at the right time, and in the proper sequence. It includes the steps, documents, tracking system, and defined approval levels needed to issue work authorizations."}
{"number":"3.4603","name":"work breakdown structure (WBS)","definitions":"a hierarchical decomposition of the total scope of work to be carried out by the project team to accomplish the project objectives and create the required deliverables"}
{"number":"3.4604","name":"work breakdown structure component","definitions":"an entry in the work breakdown structure that can be at any level"}
{"number":"3.4605","name":"work breakdown structure dictionary","definitions":"a document that provides detailed deliverable, activity, and scheduling information about each component in the work breakdown structure"}
{"number":"3.4606","name":"work effort","definitions":"labor resources required for the production of a specified output"}
{"number":"3.4607","name":"work package","definitions":"the work defined at the lowest level of the work breakdown structure for which cost and duration can be estimated and managed"}
{"number":"3.4608","name":"work performance data","definitions":"the raw observations and measurements identified during activities being performed to carry out the project work"}
{"number":"3.4609","name":"work performance information","definitions":"the performance data collected from various controlling processes, analyzed in context and integrated based on relationships across areas"}
{"number":"3.4610","name":"work performance reports","definitions":"the physical or electronic representation of work performance information compiled in project documents, intended to generate decisions, actions, or awareness"}
{"number":"3.4611","name":"work product","definitions":"artifact resulting from the execution of a process"}
{"number":"3.4612","name":"work unit","definitions":"a project task such as constructing or testing a function point, user story, feature, or requirement"}
{"number":"3.4613","name":"workaround","definitions":"a response to a threat that has occurred, for which a prior response had not been planned or was not effective"}
{"number":"3.4614","name":"workflow board","definitions":"in software development, a visual representation of work for developers who pull tasks from the task backlog; used for on-demand or resource-bound scheduling [Software Extension to the PMBOK® Guide Fifth Editio"}
{"number":"3.4615","name":"working metamodel","definitions":"definition of the specific meta-objects that can be instantiated in the model section of a CDIF transfer"}
{"number":"3.4616","name":"working set","definitions":"in the paging method of storage allocation, the set of pages that are most likely to be resident in main storage at any given point of a program's execution"}
{"number":"3.4617","name":"working space","definitions":"that portion of main storage that is assigned to a computer program for temporary storage of data"}
{"number":"3.4618","name":"workload","definitions":"mix of tasks typically run on a given computer system"}
{"number":"3.4619","name":"workload model","definitions":"model used in computer performance evaluation, depicting resource utilization and performance measures for anticipated or actual workloads in a computer system"}
{"number":"3.4620","name":"workstation","definitions":"functional unit that usually has special purpose computing capabilities and includes user-oriented input units and output units"}
{"number":"3.4621","name":"write","definitions":"to record data in a storage device or on a data medium"}
{"number":"3.4622","name":"write (-type)","definitions":"a data movement type that moves a data group lying inside the functional process to persistent storage"}
{"number":"3.4623","name":"writer","definitions":"person designing or developing user documentation"}
{"number":"3.4624","name":"writing reference","definitions":"data storage entity or other record, or interface record to another software or system to which data is written in a BFC"}
{"number":"3.4625","name":"XFN","definitions":"X/Open Federated Naming"}
{"number":"3.4626","name":"XHTML","definitions":"Extended HyperText Markup Language"}
{"number":"3.4627","name":"XMI","definitions":"XML Metadata Interchange"}
{"number":"3.4628","name":"XML","definitions":"extensible markup language"}
{"number":"3.4629","name":"XML schema definition","definitions":"XML-based language that specifies a set of rules and structure for the creation of XML documents"}
{"number":"3.4630","name":"XML schema document (XSD)","definitions":"document that describes the structure of XML information"}
{"number":"3.4631","name":"XSD","definitions":"XML schema definition"}
{"number":"3.4632","name":"yesterday's weather","definitions":"a report of work performance in the most recent reporting period"}
{"number":"3.4633","name":"zero-address instruction","definitions":"computer instruction that contains no address fields"}
